                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/243: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-08T21:00:00-03:50">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1928—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Bolivia’s answer to Paraguay’s request for convocation of Gondra Treaty was
                    to give passport to Paraguayan Minister at La Paz. Paraguay will give Bolivian
                    Minister his passport tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kreeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
